<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Architecture overview</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Simply Readable is a fully serverless application built on 11 AWS services. There are no
  servers to manage, and it scales automatically from zero to thousands of documents.
</p>

<div class="ndx-architecture-layers">
  <div class="ndx-arch-layer">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">User interface</h4>
    <div class="ndx-service-tags">
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--blue">Amazon CloudFront</span>
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--blue">Amazon S3</span>
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--blue">Amazon Cognito</span>
    </div>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      React web app served via CloudFront CDN. Authentication via Cognito User Pool.
      Static assets stored in S3.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-arch-layer">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">API layer</h4>
    <div class="ndx-service-tags">
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--turquoise">AWS AppSync</span>
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--turquoise">AWS WAF</span>
    </div>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      GraphQL API with real-time subscriptions. Protected by Web Application Firewall
      with AWS Managed Rules.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-arch-layer">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Orchestration</h4>
    <div class="ndx-service-tags">
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--green">AWS Step Functions</span>
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--green">AWS Lambda</span>
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--green">Amazon EventBridge</span>
    </div>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      Step Functions orchestrate multi-step translation and Easy Read workflows.
      Lambda functions handle individual processing tasks. EventBridge Pipes connect
      DynamoDB changes to Step Functions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-arch-layer">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">AI services</h4>
    <div class="ndx-service-tags">
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--orange">Amazon Translate</span>
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--orange">Amazon Bedrock</span>
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--orange">Amazon Comprehend</span>
    </div>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      Amazon Translate for 75+ language translation. Amazon Bedrock (Claude) for Easy Read
      text simplification. Amazon Comprehend for automatic language detection.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="ndx-arch-layer">
    <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Storage</h4>
    <div class="ndx-service-tags">
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--grey">Amazon DynamoDB</span>
      <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--grey">Amazon S3</span>
    </div>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      DynamoDB for job tracking and metadata with streams for event-driven processing.
      S3 for document storage with identity-scoped paths ensuring user isolation.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Document Translation data flow</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>User uploads a document via the React app to <strong>S3</strong> (identity-scoped path)</li>
  <li>Upload creates a job record in <strong>DynamoDB</strong></li>
  <li>DynamoDB stream triggers <strong>EventBridge Pipes</strong></li>
  <li>EventBridge starts a <strong>Step Functions</strong> workflow</li>
  <li>Step Functions calls <strong>Amazon Translate</strong> for each target language</li>
  <li>Translated files are saved back to <strong>S3</strong></li>
  <li>Job status updated in DynamoDB, user notified via <strong>AppSync</strong> subscription</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Easy Read (Simply Readable) data flow</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>User uploads a .docx file via the Simply Readable section</li>
  <li>A Lambda function converts the document to HTML, then to individual paragraphs</li>
  <li>Each paragraph is saved to <strong>DynamoDB</strong> with status "generate"</li>
  <li>DynamoDB stream triggers <strong>EventBridge Pipes</strong> (filtered to "generate" status)</li>
  <li>A <strong>Step Functions</strong> workflow sends each paragraph to <strong>Amazon Bedrock</strong></li>
  <li>Bedrock's Claude model simplifies the text into Easy Read format</li>
  <li>Simplified text is saved back to DynamoDB with status "completed"</li>
  <li>User sees original and simplified text side by side via <strong>AppSync</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Key architectural patterns</h3>

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
    <div class="ndx-pattern-card">
      <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Event-driven processing</h4>
      <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
        DynamoDB Streams + EventBridge Pipes trigger processing automatically when data changes.
        No polling, no wasted compute. This pattern scales from 1 to 10,000 documents without
        code changes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
    <div class="ndx-pattern-card">
      <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Identity-scoped storage</h4>
      <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
        Each user's documents are stored under their Cognito identity ID in S3
        (<code>private/{identity-id}/*</code>). IAM policies enforce this at the infrastructure
        level - users can only access their own documents.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

